in its own right. In the form of a prospective catalogue, it examines the practice of research-based art, using interviews and self-experiments along with media-specific forms, such as video performance and radio documentary. The project is an appeal for media arts research.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 4aMedienkunst. 4akünstlerische Forschung. 7aART / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2015z9783110438642oZDB-23-DKA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG0 cprintz978311044043040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311046088940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110460889423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110460889.jpg  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2015  aZDB-23-DKAb2015